data.name: WelcomeTextBox.Text
data.value:
Welcome to Raid Overhaul! Thanks for downloading!
If you're unsure what any config option does check the tooltip by hovering over it or check the mod page at https://forge.sp-tarkov.com/mod/1192/raid-overhaul
Happy hunting \(~,~)/

data.name: BackpackSizeCheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Changes the internal sizes of most of the backpacks in the game. Makes them all slightly (massively for boss backpacks) bigger. Useful if you intend on staying and looting in raid a lot longer with Extended Raids enabled.

data.name: GlobalChanceCheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: This lets you set a custom percent chance that Legion will spawn in your raids as opposed to using a progressive spawn chance. If disabled, the spawn chance will slowly tick up until you eventually beat the boss and it resets to it's base spawn percentage.

data.name: TraderCheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Enables the new trader. The Req Office uses new currencies to trade for almost any item in the game. The trader assort is randomly generated each server start and item prices are all either the flea or handbook price of the item to keep in line with base game balance.

data.name: customBossCheckBox.ToolTip
data.value:
Enable the custom boss "Legion" to spawn in your raids. Beating and turning in his headgear is required to unlock the Requisitions Office trader.
If disabled, the trader quest will be changed to be completeable without Legion.

data.name: WeightingExplanationTextBox.Text
data.value:
The weighting for each event is calculated as a sum. It IS NOT a percent chance.
Similar to how a lottery works, all event weightings are put together and a random number is pulled with the corresponding event set to run.
The higher an events weighting, the more likely that event "number" will be pulled.
